<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=flowerkitty&buddyTimeStamp=20050328&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fprocess_buddy.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059891&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Alicia</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Alicia lives at <a href='/home/?user=flowerkitty'>3048 Regal Mountain Drive</a>, where she is able to enjoy the magnificent views that Westridge has to offer.  Alicia has been a citizen since August 29th of 2004, and she's really enjoying her time here in Millsberry!<br><br>Alicia's classmates describe her as being quite athletic.  Her sharp eye, great physical fitness, and quick hands have earned her gold trophies for both Sink the Three and Rope Race, and in the summer you can often find her swimming laps at a pool.  One of Alicia's greatest assets as an athlete is her amazing flexibility.  If the stories her friends tell seem too good to be true, then you should head out to an ice rink during winter and check out her incredible moves for yourself.  You can easily spot Alicia on the ice, as she is usually dressed in her favorite colors of light blue, silver, and pink.  <br><br>In addition to being very athletic, Alicia does quite well in school.  Teachers at Millsberry Academy describe Alicia as being very smart, and she has Solver and Countdown trophies to prove it!  Her friends know whom to call upon whenever they have computer trouble, since Alicia has combined her interest in computers with her intelligent mind to help them on numerous occasions.  While on her own computer, Alicia often likes to look up facts about animals, as she loves learning all about them.<br><br>After school, Alicia can sometimes be found at the mall, shopping and hanging out with her friends.  They usually like to end their day by playing games at someone's house.  As you might imagine from seeing her various trophies, Alicia loves games of all sorts, and she and her friends have a great deal of fun together.<br><br>Though she loves to have fun, Alicia also devotes quite a bit of her time toward helping out in the community.  She has made a sizeable contribution to the Community Center Building Fund, which her fellow citizens certainly appreciate.  Her efforts have also played a big part in helping to keep Peabody Park clean and neat, and even the Millsberry Police Department is grateful for the aid she's provided in tracking down some of Millsberry's most dangerous criminals.<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Alicia, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
